* Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch a recording above. KEMPTON PARK - South Africa continues to be plunged into darkness as Eskom battles to keep the lights on. This week, the country seesawed between stages 4 and 6, which is the highest stage ever implemented. Eskom has partly blamed this on what it says are wildcat strikes. The utility's management is this morning giving an update on its systems challenges.